1. cs.AR (Augmented Reality): CapsuleNets have been used in augmented reality applications, and this paper proposes an energy-efficient design for CapsuleNet inference accelerators, which could be useful in AR devices. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): CapsuleNets are a type of deep neural network used in machine learning applications, and this paper proposes a specialized on-chip memory hierarchy to enable efficient CapsuleNet inference accelerators. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a methodology to explore different on-chip memory designs and a power-gating technique to reduce energy consumption, which could be useful in control systems. 
4. cs.ET (Embedded Systems): CapsuleNet inference accelerators are often used in embedded systems, and this paper proposes an energy-efficient design for on-chip memory to improve the efficiency of these accelerators. 
5. cs.EM (Emerging Technologies): CapsuleNets are a relatively new technology in the field of deep learning, and this paper proposes an energy-efficient design for CapsuleNet inference accelerators, which could be considered an emerging technology.
